{
  "texts": [
    "In orthopedic education, students can utilize generative AI tools to expand their list of differentials and initiate self-directed learning on unfamiliar diseases.",
    "Students can develop a provisional differential diagnosis by feeding necessary information from a patient's history into the AI [74].",
    "Having a tentative differential diagnosis before patient engagement can help guide a more specific history-taking and physical examination, which can then be refined and used to support diagnostic and treatment approaches.",
    "Enhancing clinical skills and reasoningProblem-based learning in medical education utilizes patient cases to improve the students' cognitive skills, enhance clinical reasoning, promote self-directed learning, encourage group discussions, and build practical scientific knowledge.",
    "Generative AI could assist in developing and refining clinical skills in orthopedics."
  ]
}